Package: cl-aserve
Version: 1.2.35
Revision: 1
Description: Portable AllegroServe Common Lisp webserver
License: LGPL
Maintainer: Lars Rosengreen <lars@margay.org>

Type: cl

Depends: clc, clisp-clc | cmucl-clc | openmcl-clc | sbcl-clc, cl-htmlgen, cl-acl-compat, cl-ppcre, cl-puri

Source: mirror:sourceforge:portableaserve/portableaserve-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: c7fc8af81f003c27ee7596f7fd2b242a

SourceDirectory: portableaserve

CompileScript: /usr/bin/true

InstallScript: <<
  find . -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \;
  find . -type f -exec chmod 644 {} \;
  rm -rf aserve/htmlgen
  mkdir -p %i/share/common-lisp/source/aserve
  cp -Rp aserve/* %i/share/common-lisp/source/aserve
  mkdir -p %i/share/common-lisp/systems
  ln -s %p/share/common-lisp/source/aserve/aserve.asd %i/share/common-lisp/systems/aserve.asd
<<

PostInstScript: %p/sbin/register-common-lisp-source aserve
PreRmScript: %p/sbin/unregister-common-lisp-source aserve

DescDetail: << 
A free and portable Common Lisp Webserver.  Portable AllegroServe is a
variant of AllegroServe(tm) with an explicit emphasis on portability
between Lispsystems and Operating Systems.  
<<

DescUsage: <<
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op 'aserve)
<<

Homepage: http://portableaserve.sourceforge.net/

